==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scall
<hw>Scall</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <ets>skalli</ets>
a bald head. Cf. <er>Scald</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>A scurf or
scabby disease, especially of the scalp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a dry <qex>scall</qex>, even a leprosy upon the head.</q>
<rj><qau>Lev. xiii. 30.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scall</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scall
<hw>Scall</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Scabby; scurfy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scalled</ent>⟦br⟧
